 
To make an autoloading object, you need to use the following code:
  this_player()->register_auto_obj("/my/crazy/path:parameter");
 
To remove an autoloading object from the player's autoload mapping:
  this_player()->remove_auto_obj("/my/crazy/path:parameter");
 
If you setup an autoloading object more than once, (for example in a guild
it would be setup in the join function and the guild object refresh function),
that would be ok, because the code in player.c makes sure that you don't add
the same object twice.
 
If you pass the optional parameter, when the object is loaded, the function
init_arg(parameter) will be called, passing the parameter to it.
 
The ":" that follows the pathname is optional.  In other words, if you have
no optional parameter, you don't need to pass the ":" when you register the
object with the player.
 
Make sure that this code doesn't exist in the object's init() function.  The
reason for this, is that if I enter a player's inventory it'll then try to add
all of his autoloading objects to me.  This code should exist in places
where the player first gets the object only.
 
